    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-13T11:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-13T11:45:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1886: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-13T11:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. A financial plan which differs in material respects from that prepared by the
                        bankers<note n="61" xml:id="d456fn61">J. &amp; W. Seligman &amp; Co. and
                        Guaranty Trust Company of New York.</note> is being prepared by Dr.
                    Cumberland. The Department may desire to transmit this information to the
                    bankers in order to avoid a duplication of effort.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
